text: Saw the movie at my local movie theatre today.  It was everything I would expect from a mainstream film..lots of crowd pleasing visuals, crowd pleasing dialogue, recognizable celebrity names, predictable dialogue and an appeal to audiences under 22 or so.  But I'm glad the movie was made as I support the movie theatre industry and if a film at the movie theatre makes money I'm glad....even if the film lacks originality or substance.  If Hustlers had been made as an independent feature they wouldn't have tried to cover so much ground.   I would give the movie a 6 out of 10 with 10 being the highest mark.
author: JACK ANTHONY
